burr
Homonym Number:  1
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a burr-bearing plant; in New Zealand, especially biddy-bid. 1. Native <i>Acaena</i> spp. esp <i>Acaena sanguisorbae</i> biddy-bid, hutiwai; an almost generic term in popular usage in early 1840s-1860s usage; replaced by biddy-bid, but still a usual general term in ref. to wool. a. Simplex : common bur(r); also native, New Zealand burr.
Origin:
